==Italian==
===Verb + pronoun===
# '''dacci''' is the Italian word caming from the  union of '''dai'' (the Italian verb [[dare#Italian|dare]] in ''subjunctive mood'', present tense, second singular person) and [[ci#Italian|ci]] (first plural person pronoun in objective case or oblique case)
:On of the possible traslation into English is ''Give us''.
:Since it is in ''subjunctive mood'' this form is used in prayer and asking. For instance this word appears in the ''Padre Nostro'' (Lat. ''Pater Noster'', Eng. ''The Lord's Prayer'') prayer: ''Dacci oggi il nostro pane quotidiano'' (Give us this day our daily bread)